          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2022-05-06 08:26:49" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>to shine or to produce light, as in the case of heavenly bodies, lightning, candles, torches, etc.</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to shine</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to give light</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to bring light</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>Terms for ‘shining, giving light’ often differ depending upon the type of source. There may be, for example, a contrast between the shining of a heavenly body in contrast with some source on earth. There may also be a difference between a continuous shining such as of the sun and the moon and a brief flash, as in the case of lightning or sparks from a fire.</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
